        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 24 at 5:15PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 515 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles northeast of Bushland, or 6 miles west of Amarillo, moving
northeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Amarillo and Bushland.

This includes Interstate 40 between mile markers 57 and 66.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
